# My dreams #

47:17.768 --> 47:21.932
After he found his bass again
in that pawn shop in Atlanta,

47:22.039 --> 47:26.942
Charlie swore
he'd never pawn it again.

47:27.044 --> 47:28.773
He swore he'd pawn
his own mother

47:28.879 --> 47:31.177
before he'd pawn that bass.

48:05.415 --> 48:09.044
Charlie.

48:09.119 --> 48:11.747
- Charlie.
- Snorts]

48:26.670 --> 48:28.228
Have you eaten anything?

48:28.305 --> 48:31.240
Uh...

48:31.308 --> 48:32.798
No.

48:32.910 --> 48:36.141
- I'll go make something.
- Oh, no, it's cool. It's cool.

48:37.481 --> 48:38.971
Why don't you sit down?

48:43.754 --> 48:47.087
Used to look out here,
you'd see one,

48:47.157 --> 48:49.990
maybe two lights.

48:50.093 --> 48:55.030
Your mom, she used to complain
all the time about being

48:55.132 --> 48:56.531
in the middle of nowhere.

49:00.671 --> 49:02.036
It's still the middle of nowhere.

49:02.139 --> 49:06.633
There's just a lot more people in it now.

49:12.316 --> 49:14.375
You didn't have to sell
your bass and records.

49:16.820 --> 49:20.347
You just have to know
when to give up.

49:20.457 --> 49:22.857
Dad, don't.

49:25.896 --> 49:29.195
I told you,
I'm finished with music.

49:32.569 --> 49:35.367
That's not what
I'm talking about.

49:46.984 --> 49:48.645
Um, excuse me.

49:48.719 --> 49:51.051
- Hi.
- Hi.

49:51.154 --> 49:52.815
Would you like to try
some chowder?

49:55.592 --> 49:58.220
So let's hear it.

49:58.328 --> 49:59.852
Okay, well, a lot of the doors

49:59.930 --> 50:02.831
claim to be alarmed
but they're not.

50:02.899 --> 50:05.060
How do you know?

50:05.168 --> 50:06.726
I opened them.

50:06.837 --> 50:07.997
Well, that's fine.

50:08.071 --> 50:10.596
We'll make a good scofflaw
out of you yet.

50:26.857 --> 50:29.121
Most of the people are really nice.

50:31.228 --> 50:32.889
Everyone says I could be looking at a raise

50:32.963 --> 50:34.863
within six months,
and the benefits are great.

50:34.931 --> 50:36.899
Hold on, here. Let's focus.

50:36.967 --> 50:39.026
Tell me about
the security guards.

50:39.102 --> 50:40.899
They have two of them.

50:40.971 --> 50:42.029
They only work in the daytime.

50:42.105 --> 50:43.367
Come on, come on!

50:43.440 --> 50:45.465
One of them is named Mike.

50:45.575 --> 50:48.237
And the other one
is named Bruce.

50:48.311 --> 50:51.075
Security guards
have master keys,

50:51.148 --> 50:53.378
but the manager,
he's the only one

50:53.450 --> 50:55.884
who has the great
grand master key.

50:55.952 --> 50:58.580
It opens every single door.

50:58.655 --> 51:00.054
He calls it the "God" key.

51:00.123 --> 51:01.886
I think you're doing great,
by the way.

51:01.958 --> 51:03.425
Thanks.

51:03.493 --> 51:07.452
Kelly and I sometimes head
out to the beach on Saturdays.

51:07.564 --> 51:09.930
We have a little barbecue,
play a little volleyball.

51:10.000 --> 51:11.900
Nah, you play volleyball.

51:11.968 --> 51:14.630
I just listen to Jimmy Buffet
and soak up the rays.

51:14.738 --> 51:17.229
I'm a total parrothead.

51:17.307 --> 51:18.501
Do you like the beach,
Miranda?

51:20.310 --> 51:22.403
I can't even remember
the last time I went to the beach.

51:22.479 --> 51:24.640
I bet you'd look great
in a bikini.

51:24.748 --> 51:26.238
Miranda.

51:26.316 --> 51:28.409
What? Let me finish the story.

51:28.485 --> 51:31.010
Did you...

51:31.121 --> 51:33.749
Did you get sort of
a weird vibe

51:33.824 --> 51:36.418
from these people?

51:36.493 --> 51:38.586
- Kind of.
- Yeah.

51:38.662 --> 51:40.926
That's because they're swingers.

51:40.997 --> 51:43.295
What?

51:43.366 --> 51:45.357
Do I gotta draw you
a picture?

51:45.469 --> 51:47.699
What are you
talking about?

51:47.804 --> 51:49.635
- You don't know, do you?
- No.

51:49.706 --> 51:54.040
So nice that you don't
know everything.

51:54.144 --> 51:56.544
Swingers, um...

51:56.646 --> 51:59.547
Well, they're, you know,
people who like

51:59.649 --> 52:02.812
to spice up their life
with different partners.

52:04.554 --> 52:05.543
Oh!

52:05.655 --> 52:07.987
Oh, my God.

52:08.058 --> 52:10.856
They were talking
swinger code.

52:10.961 --> 52:13.953
Oh, God,
that is so gross!

52:14.030 --> 52:15.224
What am I going to do?

52:15.332 --> 52:16.731
Why? Wh-What's the matter?

52:16.833 --> 52:19.666
- They invited me to a barbecue.
- They what?

52:19.736 --> 52:22.068
You were the one that told me
to accept any and all invitations

52:22.172 --> 52:24.197
so that I can get to know
the people and the layout.

52:24.307 --> 52:26.207
But I didn't mean that
you were supposed to go and...

52:26.309 --> 52:27.867
I didn't know that
they were swingers.

52:27.978 --> 52:30.139
It's cool, all right?
It's cool, it's cool.

52:30.213 --> 52:32.306
Y- You just...
You don't have to go.

52:32.382 --> 52:33.906
I told them that I would,
and, you know,

52:34.017 --> 52:35.712
I thought I could maybe
get at Doug's keys.

52:35.819 --> 52:37.252
The God key.

52:37.354 --> 52:39.914
- Yeah.
- Mm.

52:40.023 --> 52:42.048
No, no. We...
We can't do this.

52:42.159 --> 52:44.719
I think I can take care of myself, Charlie;
I've had a lot of practice.

52:44.828 --> 52:48.389
You know, sometimes
I just wish you'd call me "Dad."

52:48.498 --> 52:50.591
Okay, I can take care
of myself, Dad.

52:50.700 --> 52:53.669
Thank you. I mean, you're what,
18 years old now?

52:53.737 --> 52:55.568
I'll be 17 in 3 weeks.

52:57.207 --> 53:01.200
You're gonna be 17?
I gotta write this down, man.

53:01.278 --> 53:03.269
You are so young.

53:03.380 --> 53:04.574
But, you know,
you act so old.

53:04.681 --> 53:05.670
Sometimes you're very, um...

53:05.749 --> 53:07.376
- Precocious?
- Precocious, yes.

53:07.450 --> 53:10.283
Now, I forbid you
to go to this barbecue.

53:10.387 --> 53:11.911
You hear me?

53:12.022 --> 53:13.011
Okay, I won't.

53:13.089 --> 53:14.351
Are you going
to promise me that?

53:14.424 --> 53:16.085
Okay. God.

53:35.979 --> 53:38.743
# See the curtains
hanging in the window #

53:38.815 --> 53:44.082
# In the evening
on a Friday night #

53:44.154 --> 53:46.918
# A little light shining
through the window #

53:46.990 --> 53:52.428
# Lets me know
everything's all right #

53:52.495 --> 53:57.455
# Summer breeze
makes me feel fine #

53:57.567 --> 54:02.504
# Blowing through
the jasmine in my mind #

54:02.606 --> 54:05.837
One of the perks
of the management position:

54:05.942 --> 54:08.274
Half price on all seafood.

54:08.345 --> 54:10.074
Have some before
it's all spoiled.

54:13.083 --> 54:14.573
It's a virgin,
by the way.

54:14.651 --> 54:16.084
Berry flavored.

54:18.622 --> 54:19.919
Miranda, did you bring
your bathing suit?

54:19.990 --> 54:23.084
No. Why?

54:23.159 --> 54:24.649
You don't have
a swimming pool, right?

54:24.761 --> 54:26.592
Hot tub.

54:27.831 --> 54:31.096
- Huh. Um...
- Dude! Dude!

54:31.167 --> 54:32.691
We need some more chairs!

54:32.802 --> 54:35.600
Okay, Leonid.
Just a sec.

54:35.672 --> 54:37.469
Excuse me, ladies.

54:37.540 --> 54:40.338
Hey, so do you want to go
check out my suits?

54:40.443 --> 54:41.842
I've got a major selection.

54:41.945 --> 54:43.310
Huh?

54:43.380 --> 54:45.871
I mean, we look
like we're about the same size, huh?

54:45.982 --> 54:48.041
Uh, I think I'm...

54:48.151 --> 54:50.619
I'm sorry, I think I'm going
to have to pass on the hot tub.

54:50.687 --> 54:52.211
Are you sure?

54:52.322 --> 54:54.051
It'd be really nice.

54:54.157 --> 54:56.887
That water's, like,
fruit scented.

54:56.993 --> 54:58.790
It's pineapple...

55:00.997 --> 55:05.491
# Summer breeze
makes me feel fine #

55:05.568 --> 55:11.165
# Blowing through
the jasmine in my mind #

55:15.312 --> 55:17.576
Actually, I changed my mind.
The hot tub sounds good.

55:17.681 --> 55:21.481
It does, doesn't it?
All right, come on.

55:24.654 --> 55:28.556
So, I'm guessing
a G-string is out.

55:28.658 --> 55:30.216
What?

55:30.327 --> 55:33.228
Wait, I got the perfect thong.

55:36.900 --> 55:39.767
- A thong?
- What? Oh, no, no.

55:39.869 --> 55:41.393
- Look at this.
- No, no, no.

55:41.504 --> 55:43.165
All right.

55:43.239 --> 55:44.934
- I got it!
- Oh!

55:51.181 --> 55:53.342
- Parrots?
- Oh.

55:53.416 --> 55:55.714
Check it out.
Look at that.

55:55.785 --> 55:58.447
No? Okay.
One more.

56:02.692 --> 56:06.253
Okay, I hope you dig this.

56:06.363 --> 56:08.422
Dude!

56:08.531 --> 56:11.694
Check it out.
Look at this.

56:11.768 --> 56:15.363
Oh, hey, it's all right.

56:15.438 --> 56:18.066
Are you sure
this is a virgin?

56:19.376 --> 56:22.470
Oh, boy.

56:27.083 --> 56:29.483
You know, um,
there's this...

56:29.586 --> 56:30.985
Oh, Christ.

56:31.087 --> 56:32.486
- Oh, okay.
- I'm so sorry.

56:54.577 --> 56:56.568
- Hi.
- Hey.

56:56.646 --> 56:58.910
- What's happening?
- Ugh.

57:01.017 --> 57:06.148
So, um... look
what I got for you.

57:06.256 --> 57:09.521
One with your own name on it.

57:09.626 --> 57:11.685
Good. Great.

57:11.795 --> 57:13.126
No.

57:13.196 --> 57:14.663
Come on, your credit rating is great.

57:14.764 --> 57:17.528
No, Charlie. No.

57:17.634 --> 57:19.499
You all right?

57:19.602 --> 57:21.536
Yeah, I'm fine.

57:21.638 --> 57:24.038
So, Pepper here,
he used to work

57:24.140 --> 57:27.200
for an alarm service
company.

57:27.310 --> 57:29.278
Was that before or after
you went to jail?

57:29.345 --> 57:31.438
Before.

57:31.514 --> 57:36.975
And Pepper, he knows
how those alarm systems work.

57:40.790 --> 57:42.018
Wait, Charlie,
what did you tell him?

57:42.125 --> 57:43.114
What did he tell you?

58:27.504 --> 58:29.165
Charlie?

58:31.741 --> 58:33.208
Charlie!

58:37.547 --> 58:40.107
Is this what I think it is?

58:40.216 --> 58:42.616
Charlie, what did you do?
What is going on?

58:44.354 --> 58:46.254
Uh, I got behind
in the third mortgage.

58:46.356 --> 58:48.017
- I didn't even know there was a second.
- Well, sure.

58:48.091 --> 58:49.080
There's a third
to pay the second,

58:49.192 --> 58:50.557
a second to pay
the first, and so on.

58:50.627 --> 58:53.858
- How'd you get this?
- "And so on"?

58:53.930 --> 58:55.557
They're taking everything.

58:58.067 --> 59:02.197
Miranda, did you go
to that orgy?

59:02.272 --> 59:05.241
I... It was a barbecue.

59:08.745 --> 59:10.770
Are you sure nothing happened?

59:12.448 --> 59:14.575
Something happened, didn't it?

59:14.651 --> 59:17.984
The swingers, they
got to you, didn't they?

59:18.087 --> 59:19.645
Goddamnit!
What've I done?

59:19.756 --> 59:21.246
I'm supposed to be
your father, you know.

59:21.324 --> 59:23.383
And here I am, throwing you
right into the lion's den.

59:23.459 --> 59:25.324
You didn't.
It was my idea.

59:25.428 --> 59:27.419
Just tell me.

59:27.497 --> 59:28.896
When you went
to the bank,

59:28.965 --> 59:30.227
what was the reason
you gave them

59:30.300 --> 59:31.824
for why we needed
the money?

59:31.935 --> 59:33.903
Home improvement.

59:33.970 --> 59:35.562
Okay.

59:35.638 --> 59:36.969
What about the second time?

59:38.474 --> 59:40.339
Swimming pool.

59:40.443 --> 59:41.432
Ah.

59:41.511 --> 59:44.002
You know,
but the timing's perfect.

59:44.113 --> 59:46.081
When is the timing ever good

59:46.149 --> 59:47.810
for getting kicked out
of your house?

59:49.252 --> 59:51.777
Think about it.

59:51.854 --> 59:53.913
Yeah.

59:53.990 --> 59:57.255
It's the Chinese thing.

59:57.327 --> 01:00:03.095
Catastrophe
equals opportunity.

01:00:03.166 --> 01:00:04.155
Excuse me.

01:00:04.267 --> 01:00:05.825
It's time for you to go.

01:00:08.972 --> 01:00:10.701
"From the journal of Father Torres,

01:00:10.807 --> 01:00:14.038
"November 30, 1624.

01:00:14.143 --> 01:00:16.202
"When the savages
were silent,

01:00:16.312 --> 01:00:19.713
"that was when the company
was most affrighted.

01:00:19.816 --> 01:00:21.147
"Evidently,
they were gathered

01:00:21.217 --> 01:00:22.548
"around the entrance
to the cavern,

01:00:22.652 --> 01:00:24.210
"awaiting such time
as our hunger

01:00:24.320 --> 01:00:26.345
"might overwhelm good sense

01:00:26.456 --> 01:00:28.481
"and force us
out into the open.

01:00:32.195 --> 01:00:35.722
"Ofttimes perforce,
the officers were compelled

01:00:35.832 --> 01:00:37.390
"to use their muskets,

01:00:37.500 --> 01:00:39.900
firing over
the natives' heads."

01:00:41.738 --> 01:00:45.003
I'm getting
really good vibes here.

01:00:47.010 --> 01:00:49.342
I can't believe we're doing this.

01:00:56.819 --> 01:00:58.810
- Where are you going?
- Running away. What does it look like?

01:00:58.888 --> 01:01:00.219
We gotta stick
with the plan.

01:01:00.323 --> 01:01:02.883
- Come on!
- We gotta get out of here...

01:01:02.992 --> 01:01:05.756
Oh, God! Oh, God!
Oh, God! Oh, God!

01:01:05.862 --> 01:01:07.489
It's over here!

01:01:19.175 --> 01:01:20.836
Up here!

01:01:37.960 --> 01:01:40.121
Where's my glasses?

01:01:40.229 --> 01:01:42.595
On your head!

01:01:50.807 --> 01:01:51.967
It's done.

01:01:53.643 --> 01:01:54.905
Where's the propane?

01:01:54.977 --> 01:01:56.205
Over here!

01:02:02.485 --> 01:02:03.611
Right here!

01:02:23.473 --> 01:02:25.907
That ought to do it.

01:02:25.975 --> 01:02:26.964
Where are you going?

01:02:27.076 --> 01:02:29.909
Outside, remember?

01:02:39.155 --> 01:02:40.144
I...

01:02:40.256 --> 01:02:42.121
What are you doing?

01:02:49.699 --> 01:02:52.099
You really sure
this is going to work?

01:02:52.168 --> 01:02:54.762
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
No... No problems.

01:02:54.837 --> 01:02:58.500
Pepper, he fixed
the alarm box

01:02:58.608 --> 01:03:00.508
so it would read
like a gas leak.

01:03:00.610 --> 01:03:02.942
- And if that's the case we don't...
- Ahh!

01:03:12.622 --> 01:03:14.055
Panel says "gas leak."

01:03:14.157 --> 01:03:16.148
Smell anything?

01:03:16.225 --> 01:03:18.386
Yeah, I found it.

01:03:18.494 --> 01:03:20.485
Propane bottles leaked.

01:03:27.203 --> 01:03:28.966
Perfect.

01:03:33.976 --> 01:03:36.035
Shh, tat tat tat.

01:03:36.145 --> 01:03:40.138
I think we should
stay here for a bit.

01:03:50.993 --> 01:03:53.154
Breaking and entering
makes everything

01:03:53.229 --> 01:03:56.756
taste... different.

01:03:56.866 --> 01:04:00.199
Makes it taste,
um, livelier.

01:04:08.244 --> 01:04:13.375
In those days they would've
used pitch pine torches.

01:04:53.122 --> 01:04:57.149
It's got to be here
somewheres.

01:05:03.165 --> 01:05:04.393
Do you smell that?

01:05:04.467 --> 01:05:06.128
What?

01:05:10.339 --> 01:05:12.569
Ammonia.

01:05:12.642 --> 01:05:13.734
They must've cleaned
the floor.

01:05:13.809 --> 01:05:14.798
They cleaned your X off.

01:05:16.846 --> 01:05:19.280
That does it, then.

01:05:19.348 --> 01:05:21.748
Oh, no, I-I know
where to dig.

01:05:21.817 --> 01:05:26.186
No, it's...
it's right here.

01:05:26.289 --> 01:05:28.849
- Here?
- Yes.

01:05:28.958 --> 01:05:32.325
No, it's... it's...

01:05:33.796 --> 01:05:34.785
It's here.

01:05:34.864 --> 01:05:36.195
Charlie.

01:05:36.299 --> 01:05:38.324
Miranda, we're going
to dig here.

01:05:38.434 --> 01:05:40.766
Are you sure?

01:05:42.171 --> 01:05:44.537
Well, I... I guess I'd better be.

01:05:48.644 --> 01:05:50.168
You got the walkie talkie?

01:05:50.279 --> 01:05:51.303
Yeah.

01:05:51.380 --> 01:05:53.371
Pepper, is it all clear?

01:05:55.151 --> 01:05:56.175
Yeah.

01:06:42.598 --> 01:06:43.656
Come in, Charlie.

01:06:43.733 --> 01:06:46.600
Charlie, come in.

01:07:00.683 --> 01:07:02.514
Evening, sir.

01:07:02.585 --> 01:07:04.553
What seems to be
the problem?

01:07:04.620 --> 01:07:06.019
Motorcycle's not working?

01:07:08.024 --> 01:07:09.582
We hit rebar.

01:07:09.692 --> 01:07:12.456
Well, I think
I might've flooded it.

01:07:18.134 --> 01:07:19.965
There's the throttle
right there.

01:07:20.069 --> 01:07:21.536
I know. I know.

01:07:32.214 --> 01:07:34.045
Hey, let me try.

01:07:38.387 --> 01:07:40.753
Hey!

01:08:48.491 --> 01:08:50.890
Miranda.

01:08:50.993 --> 01:08:52.483
Hey.

01:09:02.971 --> 01:09:04.997
Don't step on that.

01:09:13.582 --> 01:09:15.482
Hello.

01:09:44.246 --> 01:09:46.510
- Ugh!
- Hmm.

01:09:46.582 --> 01:09:48.845
What is that smell?

01:09:48.917 --> 01:09:52.081
- Ugh.
- You must've hit the sewer line.

01:09:52.188 --> 01:09:55.715
No, the sewer's all the way
on the other side of the store,

01:09:55.791 --> 01:09:57.019
under pet care.

01:10:02.031 --> 01:10:04.056
Current is stronger
than I thought it'd be.

01:10:05.534 --> 01:10:08.264
That looks a lot
like sewage to me.

01:10:10.940 --> 01:10:13.636
It's the underground river.

01:10:13.742 --> 01:10:16.210
Just like the journal
said it would be.

01:10:19.715 --> 01:10:21.376
Where are you going?

01:10:21.450 --> 01:10:23.111
Sir!

01:10:23.219 --> 01:10:26.882
Come on, sir,
you're just wasting gas.

01:10:39.001 --> 01:10:40.229
Pepper.

01:10:45.107 --> 01:10:48.235
Come in, Pepper.

01:10:49.678 --> 01:10:50.736
Charlie?

01:10:50.813 --> 01:10:54.078
This store is great.
It's got everything.

01:10:54.149 --> 01:10:55.741
What are you doing?

01:10:55.818 --> 01:10:57.581
That should
be long enough.

01:10:57.653 --> 01:11:02.590
The journal says the passageway's
about 40 barras.

01:11:02.658 --> 01:11:04.523
That's Spanish for "yards".

01:11:04.627 --> 01:11:06.754
So it should be
about 120 feet.

01:11:06.829 --> 01:11:09.297
People get killed all the time
doing stuff like this.

01:11:09.365 --> 01:11:11.925
I need you to hold
the other end tightly.

01:11:12.001 --> 01:11:14.765
Stop! You're jumping
into raw sewage.

01:11:14.837 --> 01:11:18.534
This is not sewage, okay?
It's sulfur.

01:11:18.641 --> 01:11:20.802
I noticed before
when I tested the water,

01:11:20.876 --> 01:11:23.470
it's warmer than
the room temperature.

01:11:23.545 --> 01:11:27.606
And this brown color indicates
an iron sulfite hot springs.

01:11:27.683 --> 01:11:28.672
There's no reasoning with you.

01:11:28.784 --> 01:11:30.217
You have an answer
for everything.

01:11:30.319 --> 01:11:32.184
That really bothers you.

01:11:32.288 --> 01:11:34.279
I was hoping that I wasn't
going to have to say this.

01:11:34.356 --> 01:11:36.187
- What?
- Don't make me say it.

01:11:36.292 --> 01:11:37.486
All right, then.

01:11:40.162 --> 01:11:42.027
There's no gold, okay?

01:11:42.131 --> 01:11:43.120
There's no treasure.

01:11:43.198 --> 01:11:45.393
You're about to jump
into a sewer.

01:11:45.501 --> 01:11:47.833
This whole thing
is a delusion.

01:11:59.014 --> 01:12:02.541
Sir, put your arms
out to your sides.

01:12:02.651 --> 01:12:05.848
Sir... put your arms
all the way out to your sides,

